-- China Property Tax May Cause Pullback in Home Prices, Credit Suisse Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-29T01:07:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/china-property-tax-may-cause-pullback-for-stock-market-credit-suisse-says.html
The Chinese government may
implement a property tax in some cities soon with Shanghai,
Shenzhen and Chongqing the most likely candidates, according to
Credit Suisse Group AG.  Credit Suisse recommended “reducing exposure” to Chinese
property stocks in the near term, saying a tax would hurt real-
estate market sentiment and property stocks’ performance,
analysts led by Jinsong Du wrote in a note to clients.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  